    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nNavigating/editing markdown buffers with `conceallevel=2` set is slow.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `seq 1 1000|sed 's/$/ some **bold text**/' > /tmp/foo.md`\n2. `nvim --clean +'set conceallevel=2' /tmp/foo.md`\n3. Hold down `C-d` for scrolling -> very laggy.\n4. Press `i` and *quickly* insert text, i.e. type fast -> very laggy. I guess I could spam characters for a whole minute without any (visual) buffer updates, only once I pause for about half a second the characters appear in the buffer.\n\nI noticed that after the laggy scrolling down with `C-d`, scrolling up with `C-u` is fast again. However, after a buffer change it's slow again.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nEverything is fast :)\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev-452+g0976ce255b\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.2.388\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArchlinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nfoot version: 1.26.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nfoot\n\n### Installation\n\nAppimage",
    "closed_at": null,
