        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "threw AI at problem: https://github.com/alf171/neovim/commit/f229d5fc1a40f3a513d507aacafb906a3e978573. pretty interesting suggestions. I'm going to avoid making a commit b/c i don't really understand the conceal code well enough, even though tests seem to pass and the performance is noticeably better. \n\nCrux of it is:\nWhen checking whether a line should be completely hidden, we run the tree-sitter highlighter’s `_on_conceal_line` callback. Before, that path could run highlight queries that only define character-level conceal rules, such as hiding ** in markdown, even though they can never define conceal_lines.\n\nThis change skips those irrelevant queries I believe.",
